From: Claude (devcontainer agent)
Date: 2026-04-26
Subject: [C1] post_install.py: do not write hasCompletedOnboarding=true on
         claude -p failure or corrupt config

Why this is a separate patch
============================
This devcontainer mounts /workspace/.devcontainer as read-only inside the
container, so an agent running inside cannot edit post_install.py directly.
Apply this patch from the host (or any environment with write access to
.devcontainer/), then commit and push.

What this fixes (review item C1)
================================
Two failure modes silently overwrite ~/.claude.json with
{"hasCompletedOnboarding": true}, masking auth failures and destroying
recovery state:

1. `claude -p` returncode != 0: the function prints the error but does not
   return — flow continues to the JSON write. If the existing
   ~/.claude.json is a valid stale config from a prior run, it gets
   clobbered with no auth state, so the next `claude` invocation skips
   onboarding and fails with a confusing "not authenticated" error
   instead of re-running the wizard.

2. JSONDecodeError on existing ~/.claude.json: the corrupt original is
   silently overwritten, destroying any partially recoverable
   auth/MCP/session state before the user knows about it.

The patch returns early after non-zero `claude -p` exit (the existing
content stays put), and on JSONDecodeError moves the corrupt file to
~/.claude.json.bak before continuing — so the user can inspect and recover.

How to apply
============
From a shell on the host (NOT inside the devcontainer):

  cd <smudge repo root>
  git apply paad/code-reviews/deferred/C1-post_install-onboarding-bypass.patch
  git add .devcontainer/post_install.py
  git commit -m "fix(devcontainer): preserve ~/.claude.json on claude -p failure or corrupt config (C1)"

Then push and continue with the remaining review items applied from inside
the container.

---
diff --git a/.devcontainer/post_install.py b/.devcontainer/post_install.py
--- a/.devcontainer/post_install.py
+++ b/.devcontainer/post_install.py
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@
 import contextlib
 import json
 import os
+import shutil
 import subprocess
 import sys
 from pathlib import Path
@@ -49,12 +50,20 @@ def setup_onboarding_bypass():
             text=True,
             timeout=30,
         )
         if result.returncode != 0:
+            # C1 (review 2026-04-26): bail out without touching
+            # ~/.claude.json. Falling through here would write
+            # {hasCompletedOnboarding: true} over a stale-but-valid
+            # config (from a prior successful run), masking the auth
+            # failure: subsequent `claude` invocations would skip
+            # onboarding and fail with a confusing "not authenticated"
+            # error instead of re-running the wizard.
             print(
                 f"[post_install] claude -p exited {result.returncode}: "
-                f"{result.stderr.strip()}",
+                f"{result.stderr.strip()} — onboarding bypass skipped",
                 file=sys.stderr,
             )
+            return
     except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:
         print(
             "[post_install] claude -p timed out (expected on cold start)",
@@ -76,11 +85,29 @@ def setup_onboarding_bypass():
     config: dict = {}
     try:
         config = json.loads(claude_json.read_text())
     except json.JSONDecodeError as e:
-        print(
-            f"[post_install] Warning: {claude_json} has invalid JSON ({e}), "
-            "starting fresh",
-            file=sys.stderr,
-        )
+        # C1 (review 2026-04-26): a corrupt config may still hold partially
+        # recoverable auth/MCP/session state. Move it aside before we write
+        # over it so the user can inspect/recover, rather than silently
+        # destroying it.
+        backup = claude_json.with_suffix(claude_json.suffix + ".bak")
+        try:
+            shutil.move(str(claude_json), str(backup))
+            print(
+                f"[post_install] Warning: {claude_json} had invalid JSON "
+                f"({e}); backed up to {backup} and starting fresh",
+                file=sys.stderr,
+            )
+        except OSError as move_err:
+            print(
+                f"[post_install] Warning: {claude_json} had invalid JSON "
+                f"({e}) and could not be backed up ({move_err}) — "
+                "onboarding bypass skipped to preserve the original file",
+                file=sys.stderr,
+            )
+            return

     config["hasCompletedOnboarding"] = True

     claude_json.write_text(json.dumps(config, indent=2) + "\n", encoding="utf-8")
